## 1.01 truffle vscode and remix

1. Install VSCode
- Download from https://code.visualstudio.com/

2. Install Golang 
https://go.dev/dl/

3. Open 1.01-truffle-vscode-remix with VSCode then open terminal

4. Install node via nvm
- Install nvm https://github.com/nvm-sh/nvm
- Install nodejs using nvm
$ curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvm-sh/nvm/v0.39.0/install.sh | bash
$ nvm ls
$ nvm install v16.13.1
$ nvm use v16.13.1
$ node -v
$ v16.13.1

4.1 We recommended you to install via nvm BUT IF YOU CANNOT INSTALL NVM, go to node download and download v16.13.1 version

- To make sure that all workshop is the same as in the video, make sure to use node v16.13.1 (LTS)
$ node -v
v16.13.1

5. Install yarn
- Install yarn https://classic.yarnpkg.com/en/docs/install
$ npm install --global yarn
$ yarn -v
1.22.10

6. Install Truffle
$ yarn global add truffle

7. Init truffle project
$ truffle init

8. Explain directory structure of truffle project
/contracts
/migrations
/test
truffle-config.js

9. Compile truffle project
$ truffle compile

10. Open remix
- https://remix.ethereum.org/

11. Create file in remix named Helloworld.sol and place content in Helloworld.sol in remix editor

12. Explain how to compile and deploy in remix